rs,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "which swim,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "glide along,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tasobaHu", "text_ar": "تَسْبَحُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in the firmament, like the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "saAbiH", "text_ar": "سَابِح"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in water."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) [The meanings"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "fœminæ jejunantes"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "veloces equi"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "planetæ,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "assigned to this word by Golius as on the authority of the KL, are in that work assigned to"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "saAy^iHaAt", "text_ar": "سَايِحَات"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; the first of them as the meaning of this word in the Kur lxvi. 5.] And you say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "nujuwmN sawaAbiHu", "text_ar": "نُجُومٌ سَوَابِحُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Stars gliding along"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in the firmament:"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "swAbH", "text_ar": "سوابح"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "being a pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "saAbiHN", "text_ar": "سَابِحٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "applied to an irrational thing, and of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "saAbiHapN", "text_ar": "سَابِحَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (A.) ―         -b3-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "saAbiHN", "text_ar": "سَابِحٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is also applied as an epithet to a horse, (S, IAth, A, L,) meaning (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "That stretches forth his fore legs well in running"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "like as one does the arms in swimming"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (S, * IAth, L;) and in like manner ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sabuwHN", "text_ar": "سَبُوحٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[but in an intensive sense]: (A, L:) the pl. [of the former] is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sawaAbiHu", "text_ar": "سَوَابِحُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sub~aHN", "text_ar": "سُبَّحٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (A.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sawaAbiHu", "text_ar": "سَوَابِحُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also signified (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Horses;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA;) as an epithet in which the quality of a subst. is predominant; (TA;) because they thus stretch forth their fore legs in running. (K, * TA.) Hence, (TA,) ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Als~abuwHu", "text_ar": "السَّبُوحُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is the name of"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A horse of Rabeea Ibn-Jusham."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA.) And in like manner, ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Als~ab~aAHu", "text_ar": "السَّبَّاحُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is the name of"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A celebrated courser:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:) and of"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A certain camel."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA.)"}], "source_refs": ["Msb", "K", "MF", "TA", "S", "IAth", "A", "L"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}